Introduction 

In the modern era, being "digitally literate" is no longer just an optional skill; it is a fundamental requirement for any engineering student. Digital literacy involves the ability to find, evaluate, and communicate information through various digital platforms effectively and safely. As a Student Digital Ambassador, I have undertaken this project to demonstrate my proficiency in professional networking, technical problem-solving, and cyber-security awareness. This report summarizes the five key tasks I completed, reflecting on the tools used and the digital competencies gained.

Task 1: Digital Literacy Awareness Infographic

Reflection: For Task 1, I designed an infographic using Canva to visually explain the core pillars of digital literacy. I focused on three main areas: the definition of digital literacy, essential tools for students (like GitHub and Google Workspace), and basic online safety tips. Creating this visual forced me to condense complex ideas into simple, punchy points that anyone could understand. I learned that as a Digital Ambassador, my job is to make technology less intimidating for others. Choosing the right layout and icons was a great exercise in digital communication and design thinking.

Task 2: Professional Portfolio

Reflection: In this task, I focused on building my professional digital identity. I set up my GitHub repository to host my projects, updated my LinkedIn profile to connect with industry professionals, and created a Kaggle profile for data science exploration. I’ve realized that a professional online presence acts as a digital resume that works for you even when you're offline. Setting up the GitHub README specifically taught me how to document my work professionally using Markdown, which is a vital skill for any developer today.

Task 3: Interactive Platforms & Data Management

Reflection: Task 3 was about using interactive platforms for technical and administrative work. I solved a coding challenge on HackerRank, which tested my logical thinking and taught me how automated platforms evaluate code. I also created a Google Form quiz to collect data on cyber-safety awareness. By linking this form to Google Sheets, I saw how digital tools can automate data organization, removing the need for manual entry. This task showed me how a Digital Ambassador can use simple tools to gather and analyze information from a large community quickly.

Task 4: Digital Etiquette (Netiquette)

Reflection: This task focused on "Netiquette"—the code of conduct for the digital world. I drafted two professional emails: one requesting a deadline extension and another inquiring about an internship. This taught me the importance of a clear subject line and a respectful tone in professional correspondence. I also created a "Do’s and Don’ts" list for social media. I’ve learned that everything we post contributes to our "digital footprint." Maintaining a clean, secure, and professional image online is essential for long-term career success and personal safety.

Task 5: Cybercrime Case Study & Prevention

Reflection: For the final task, I researched a case study on Phishing—one of the most common cybercrimes today. Analyzing how attackers use psychological manipulation to steal data was eye-opening. I created an 8-tip prevention checklist, including practices like using Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) and checking sender addresses. This task was the most impactful because it moved beyond just using tools to understanding the risks associated with them. As a Digital Ambassador, I now feel better equipped to protect myself and advise my peers on staying safe in an increasingly dangerous digital landscape.

Conclusion
Completing this project has significantly broadened my understanding of what it means to be digitally literate. I  have progressed from being a simple consumer of digital content to a creator and an ambassador of digital safety and professionalism. From mastering GitHub's folder structure to understanding the nuances of professional email etiquette, these skills will serve as a strong foundation for my B.Tech journey and my future professional car
